The paper deals with communication over a Gaussian multiple access channel with secrecy constraints, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed scheme is based on lattice alignment, which is a technique commonly used in network coding (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also includes numerical analysis, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) if the results are presented visually.
